rComments: I don't understand why people seem to like her. I found her condescending. This class has effectively sucked the desire to continue Japanese out of me.

A teacher who is very passionate about her job, which makes the classes enjoyable for those who are serious about learning Japanese. There are a lot of stuff to study and daily quizzes, but if you put in the time, they won't be difficult at all. However, I would not recommend the course for those who are looking for easy credit.

She is an amazing lecturer and her classes are super entertaining. She seems so passionate about her job and that makes the course very enjoyable. With that said so, this is definitely not a bird course. You get homework and quiz every week and she checks attendance every time. For those who has no Asian background, this course may be tough.
BEST_PROF_EVER. She is so helpful and passionate about our learning. I was able to step out of my comfort zone and even learned more about myself.
Really cheerful and helpful teacher, she made my classes lots of fun to go to~ Lectures tend to be a lot to take in at once though, so it helps to review with the textbook.
